                            <comment id="13752665" author="sbtourist" created="Wed, 28 Aug 2013 18:22:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch with StreamOut fix and a related test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13752759" author="yukim" created="Wed, 28 Aug 2013 19:28:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;br/&gt;
This is regression caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5569&quot; title=&quot;Every stream operation requires checking indexes in every SSTable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13753716" author="yukim" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 15:21:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13758245" author="rbranson" created="Wed, 4 Sep 2013 19:28:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Curious what the impact of this would have been? Has streaming effectively been broken since 1.2.6, since every cluster has wrapping ranges?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13758484" author="yukim" created="Wed, 4 Sep 2013 22:54:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rbranson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rbranson&quot;&gt;rbranson&lt;/a&gt; It only affects bootstrap/decommission/move of wrapping range, since only those use transferRanges. If you do repair after bootstrap or move, then it will sync unfetched data.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
